  "texts": [
    "Additionally, a Fine Region Proposal Network (FRPN) based on the color features of traffic signs was established.",
    "FRPN generated the final region proposals for each feature map position extracted by the attention network.",
    "Furthermore, they added deconvolution structures in the convolutional layers to adapt to small-sized targets.Reference [32] proposed an enhanced YOLOV4-Tiny traffic sign recognition algorithm, which solved the difficulties of the existing models, such as a high number of parameters, slow detection speed, and low recognition accuracy.",
    "By combining the YOLOV4-Tiny backbone network with Octave Convolution and adding the Convolutional Block Attention Module (CBAM), they improved the accuracy of traffic sign recognition.",
    "The algorithm achieves high average precision (AP) and frames per second (FPS) on the TT100K and CCTSDB datasets while reducing computational complexity and model size to meet the requirements of real-time traffic sign recognition."
  ],
